New Records: Paolo Banchero scored 34 points in his return after missing 34 games with an oblique injury
Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo led all scorers with 41 points, Paolo Banchero scored 12 of Orlando's final 14 points
Pre-Game Insights: Banchero was off to an outstanding start in his first five games, including a 50-point effort on Oct. 28
Post-Match Reflections: Banchero's absence did make a difference, Orlando's scoring average dropped from 112.2 points per game to 103.7
Miscellaneous Highlights: Orlando hosts the Philadelphia 76ers on Sunday, Milwaukee travels to New York for a matinee versus the Knicks
Others: Jett Howard left the game in the fourth quarter with a left ankle sprain, Jalen Suggs was sidelined with a lower back strain
